at least one new\n  transcript record.\n- `TurnDetail.records` is an ordered array and is authoritative for rendering\n  order within the capture turn.\n- Backfilled capture turns may contain many logical conversation/provider turns,\n  so records must carry provider/display grouping metadata when available.\n- `turn_key` is `sha256-<32 lowercase hex chars>`, computed from UTF-8 stored\n  `session_key`, `s\n[TRUNCATED]\npture invocation\n5. record which transcript records belong to the capture turn\n6. record enough repository environment state to support later association\n\nCreate a capture turn only when capture writes at least one new transcript\nrecord. An environment-only observation should not create a capture turn.\nOtherwise the model drifts from agent-session capture into repository telemetry.\n\nThe first hook run for a session may capture more than one actual conversation\nturn if it imports an existing transcript backlog. Later stop-hook runs should\nusually map more closely to one user/agent interaction. That distinction should\nstay visible in the model: a capture turn is a capture observation, not\nnecessarily a provider-native turn.\n\nFor first-time backfill, create one capture turn containing all newly written\nrecords and one environment snapshot from capture time. Provider-native turn\nidentifiers, when available, can be preserved as optional record-level grouping\nmetadata, but they should not become real capture turns during backfill because\nhistorical repository environment snapshots cannot be reconstructed.\n\nStore a compact `capture_kind` on the capture turn:\n\n- `backfill`: the capture imported an existing transcript backlog\n- `incremental`: the capture observed new records from an ongoing session\n\nBackfill turns are valid transcript history, but their environment snapshot is\nweaker association evidence because it only describes capture time, not the time\neach historical provider turn happened.\n\nBackfill must still be readable. Record parsing should preserve enough grouping\nmetadata for handoff and review UIs to render logical conversation turns inside\nthe backfill capture turn:\n\n- provider turn key when the source provides one\n- otherwise a derived display group based on user-message boundaries and record\n  order\n\n## Capture Turn Data\n\nA capture turn needs a stable ID for idempotent repeated capture. Given a\ncapture turn, it should be possible to find the transcript records that were\nnewly observed in that turn.\n\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-20T17:24:53.727Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}